=======
libecat
=======
 
libecat (z_matrix_70) is a c library for reading and writing CTI PET
data sets.  It was written by CTI, with extensions and some utils
added by Merence Sibomona <Sibomana@topo.ucl.ac.be> and company.

This library is released under a restricive non-free license (see
orig_src/copyright).  The library is free to use for non-commercial
uses.

This version is intended to be used with amide, and can be found at:
	http://amide.sourceforge.net

The original libecat site is:
        ftp://dormeur.topo.ucl.ac.be/pub/ecat/z_matrix_70/ecat.tar.gz
 

The major difference in the amide version of libecat (i.e. this
version) is that it includes configure scripts and Makefiles to build
libecat as a shared library.  This is done because distributing a
statically linked binary version of amide is illegal due to the
incompatibilities of the license that amide is distributed under (GPL)
and the license libecat is released under (see orig_src/copyright).

Additionally, several minor changes have been made to the library,
mainly to allow it to work on Mac OS X (darwin) in addition to Linux.
All changes to libecat are distributed as a patch to the original
source, as the copyright does not allow distribution of the original
source code in a modified form.

Take care,
	Andy Loening <loening@alum.mit.edu>

 
Building
--------
  
        ./configure
        make
        make install      
	/sbin/ldconfig


You'll have to be root for the last two commands.
